As of December 31, 2022 , we had federal, state, and foreign net operating loss carryovers, which will reduce future taxable income when utilized. Approximately $ 66.2 million in net federal tax benefit is available from the loss carryovers and an additional $ 0.3 million is available in tax credit carryovers. $ 14.8 million of the federal net operating loss tax benefit will expire from 2031 to 2037 . The remaining $ 51.4 million has an indefinite carryover period. The state loss carryovers and foreign loss carryovers will result in a tax benefit of approximately $ 32.5 million and $ 22.1 million, respectively, when utilized. The state net operating loss carryovers will begin to expire in 2023 . The majority of the foreign operating loss carryovers have an indefinite carryover period. The $ 0.3 million tax credit carryover is composed of a variety of credits most of which expire between 2027 and 2042 . 

